|CD]], [[Gramophone record|LP]], [[Music download|DL]]\n| 1 || 1 || 2 || 2 || 17 || 1 || 3 || 1 || 1 || 2\n|\n* UK: 2,358,380<ref name=UKAlbumSale>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/official-charts-analysis-sam-smith-debuts-at-no-1-just-short-of-100-000-sales/070455|title=Official Charts Analysis: Sam Smith debuts at No.1 just short of 100,000 sales|work=[[Music Week]]|author=Alan Jones|date=10 November 2017|accessdate=12 November 2017<!--Quote from the article: \"In The Lonely Hour jumps 21-15 (6,821 sales) this week to achieve its highest chart position for nearly two years, and with cumulative sales of 2,358,380 it is the second biggest selling debut album of the 2010s\"-->}}</ref>\n* US: 4,400,000 <small>([[Album-equivalent unit|AEU]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7989309/sam-smith-interview-billboard-2017|title=Sam Smith on His Recent Struggles, Triumphant Return and Having His Eyes Opened in Iraq|work=Billboard|author=Nick Duerden|date=6 October 2017|accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref>\n* WW: 12,000,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/sir-lucian-grainge-people-said-music-industry-didnt-listen/|title=Sir Lucian Grainge: \u2018When people said the music industry was over, we didn\u2019t listen.\u2019|author=Tim Ingham|date=10 August 2017|accessdate=3 October 2017|publisher=MBW}}</ref>\n|\n* [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]]: 8\u00d7 Platinum<ref name=\"BPI\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bpi.co.uk/brit-certified/|title=BRIT Certified - bpi|publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry]]|accessdate=11 May 2019|format=To access, enter the search parameter \"Sam Smith\"}}</ref>\n* [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]]: 5\u00d7 Platinum<ref>{{cite certification|region=Australia|type=album|certyear=2017|accessdate=4 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Bundesverband Musikindustrie|BVMI]]: Gold<ref name=\"BVMI\">{{cite certification|region=Germany|artist=Sam Smith|type=a